00:46:03,887 --> 00:46:04,763
What is it?

654
00:46:05,931 --> 00:46:07,349
What have you done to your hair?

655
00:46:08,516 --> 00:46:11,019
- Nothing. Why?
- You're looking good.

656
00:46:34,459 --> 00:46:36,419
- You lost your keys?
- No.

657
00:46:50,183 --> 00:46:52,686
Hello. My father has
an appointment with Dr. Sarai.

658
00:46:54,229 --> 00:46:56,147
Dad, come here.

659
00:47:06,157 --> 00:47:07,450
Okay, thank you.

660
00:47:07,534 --> 00:47:09,494
So it's you who signs there.

661
00:47:11,162 --> 00:47:12,664
I can fill in these.

662
00:47:14,541 --> 00:47:15,542
Date of birth?

663
00:47:16,126 --> 00:47:19,004
Friday, 31st of December, 1937.

664
00:47:19,587 --> 00:47:21,047
- Friday?
- Yes.

665
00:47:21,798 --> 00:47:24,426
You're living with your daughter
at the moment, is that right?

666
00:47:24,509 --> 00:47:26,928
Yes. Until she goes to live in Paris.

667
00:47:27,470 --> 00:47:29,556
No, Dad, why do you keep
going on about Paris?

668
00:47:30,181 --> 00:47:32,392
- What?
- I'm staying in London.

669
00:47:34,352 --> 00:47:37,272
You keep changing your mind.
How do you expect people to keep up?

670
00:47:37,355 --> 00:47:39,315
Never been any question
of me living in Paris.

671
00:47:39,399 --> 00:47:41,317
- Yes, there was. You told me.
- No, I didn't.

672
00:47:41,401 --> 00:47:43,194
I'm sorry. You told me the other day.

673
00:47:43,778 --> 00:47:45,905
Have you forgotten? She's forgotten.

674
00:47:46,448 --> 00:47:49,743
You're suffering from memory loss.
I'd have a word with the doctor.

675
00:47:49,826 --> 00:47:52,829
- In any event, I'm not going to Paris.
- That's good.

676
00:47:52,912 --> 00:47:55,457
Paris. They don't even
speak English there.

677
00:48:11,056 --> 00:48:14,225
I know how worrying these things can be,
and things can change very quickly.

678
00:48:14,309 --> 00:48:17,937
So if you need anything at all,
give me a call. Any time.

679
00:48:18,021 --> 00:48:20,148
Thank you. Thank you for your help.

680
00:48:52,931 --> 00:48:53,765
Dad?

681
00:50:40,955 --> 00:50:42,081
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

682
00:50:42,624 --> 00:50:43,458
Thank you.

683
00:50:48,004 --> 00:50:49,255
Hello. What's the matter?

684
00:50:50,465 --> 00:50:51,299
What?

685
00:50:52,842 --> 00:50:55,220
All right. I'll be up in a minute.

686
00:50:58,431 --> 00:50:59,933
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

687
00:51:00,016 --> 00:51:00,850
Sorry.

688
00:51:06,272 --> 00:51:07,190
What's happening?

689
00:51:09,067 --> 00:51:11,277
Nothing much,
but I think he'd like to see you.

690
00:51:11,903 --> 00:51:13,446
- Where is he?
- In his room.

691
00:51:14,364 --> 00:51:15,698
- Let me have it.
- Thank you.

692
00:51:42,267 --> 00:51:43,476
Here, let me.

693
00:51:45,228 --> 00:51:46,229
What have you done?

694
00:52:05,206 --> 00:52:06,291
What's the matter?

695
00:52:06,916 --> 00:52:07,750
Nothing.

696
00:52:12,171 --> 00:52:14,299
Okay. I'll get dinner ready.

697
00:52:15,550 --> 00:52:16,384
Anne?

698
00:52:17,510 --> 00:52:19,554
- What?
- Thank you for everything.

699
00:53:12,607 --> 00:53:15,360
- We have to find another arrangement.
- Such as?

700
00:53:15,443 --> 00:53:17,278
- Putting him in an institution.
- A home?

701
00:53:17,362 --> 00:53:18,988
Yes, a nursing home.

702
00:53:19,864 --> 00:53:21,032
It'd be better for him.

703
00:53:21,115 --> 00:53:24,869
Why are you saying this now?
Tomorrow we've got this girl starting.

704
00:53:24,952 --> 00:53:26,329
You're right.

705
00:53:26,412 --> 00:53:29,665
We'll see. Maybe it'll work out
very well with this girl.

706
00:53:29,749 --> 00:53:31,042
You seem to think she's good.

707
00:53:31,125 --> 00:53:33,378
But, believe me, the doctor is right.

708
00:53:33,461 --> 00:53:38,132
The moment will come when--
However good she is, he's ill, Anne.

709
00:53:38,966 --> 00:53:40,009
He's ill.

710
00:53:42,220 --> 00:53:45,223
Dad, what are you doing
standing out there? Come on.

711
00:53:47,892 --> 00:53:49,560
Come on. Come and sit down.

