01:18:03,930 --> 01:18:06,057
Dad? Can I talk to you?

1032
01:18:13,273 --> 01:18:14,274
How shall I put this?

1033
01:18:16,985 --> 01:18:21,364
Do you remember the first time
you came to stay with me? It was just--

1034
01:18:21,447 --> 01:18:24,951
It was a stopgap because you'd
fallen out with Angela and...

1035
01:18:28,079 --> 01:18:29,831
I was wondering if it might be better...

1036
01:18:32,709 --> 01:18:34,878
What do you think of this room?
It's nice, isn't it?

1037
01:18:36,170 --> 01:18:38,339
- You can see the park.
- Can you?

1038
01:18:44,554 --> 01:18:45,847
It's very nice.

1039
01:18:48,766 --> 01:18:51,060
It's a bit like being in a hotel,
don't you think?

1040
01:18:51,561 --> 01:18:52,812
All the residents say so.

1041
01:18:58,151 --> 01:19:01,195
I think you'd be better <i>off</i> here.

1042
01:19:03,281 --> 01:19:04,115
Where?

1043
01:19:05,533 --> 01:19:06,367
Here.

1044
01:19:07,368 --> 01:19:10,914
I think it'd be more reassuring
and nicer for you

1045
01:19:10,997 --> 01:19:14,208
if we came to a joint decision
about you living here.

1046
01:19:15,710 --> 01:19:16,711
What do you think?

1047
01:19:19,172 --> 01:19:22,342
Well, what about you?
What would you do? Where...?

1048
01:19:23,718 --> 01:19:26,262
Where would you sleep? Which room?

1049
01:19:26,346 --> 01:19:29,515
Well, if you remember,
I'm gonna go and live in Paris.

1050
01:19:32,810 --> 01:19:33,895
No, you're not.

1051
01:19:35,521 --> 01:19:36,648
I am. Remember?

1052
01:19:36,731 --> 01:19:38,775
I told you all about it. Remember?

1053
01:19:39,734 --> 01:19:40,735
But you said...

1054
01:19:41,736 --> 01:19:43,529
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

1055
01:19:46,741 --> 01:19:48,034
But you told me...

1056
01:19:49,077 --> 01:19:50,662
you were staying here with me.

1057
01:19:52,121 --> 01:19:54,290
No, I have to go. It is important.

1058
01:19:54,374 --> 01:19:56,000
I explained it all to you.

1059
01:19:56,084 --> 01:19:58,670
I'll come back and see you,
occasional weekends.

1060
01:20:04,050 --> 01:20:05,218
What about me?

1061
01:20:08,763 --> 01:20:10,890
You're going to stay here in London.

1062
01:20:12,183 --> 01:20:13,351
All on my own?

1063
01:20:15,269 --> 01:20:18,356
- What about your sister? Where is she?
- Oh, Dad.

1064
01:20:19,315 --> 01:20:21,526
If you only knew how much I miss her.

1065
01:20:23,111 --> 01:20:26,322
I do too. I miss her too, Dad.
We all miss her.

1066
01:22:59,058 --> 01:22:59,892
Anne?

1067
01:23:27,044 --> 01:23:27,962
Sleep well?

1068
01:23:29,088 --> 01:23:30,506
What am I doing here?

1069
01:23:32,049 --> 01:23:32,925
It's time.

1070
01:23:33,009 --> 01:23:36,262
I didn't ask about the time.
I asked you what I was doing here.

1071
01:23:36,345 --> 01:23:37,555
Where's Anne?

1072
01:23:38,306 --> 01:23:40,016
I've brought you your medication.

1073
01:23:40,099 --> 01:23:42,935
Why don't you just fuck off
with your medication?

1074
01:23:43,019 --> 01:23:44,729
- Are you a nurse?
- Yeah.

1075
01:23:44,812 --> 01:23:47,607
Oh, you are. Oh, I see. That's it.

1076
01:23:48,357 --> 01:23:49,400
You are a nurse.

1077
01:23:49,483 --> 01:23:50,359
Yes.

1078
01:23:50,443 --> 01:23:53,529
That's what I was thinking.
You're the type. Typical nurse.

1079
01:23:53,613 --> 01:23:55,448
So, what are you doing here?

1080
01:23:56,073 --> 01:23:58,701
- Sorry?
- What are you doing here?

1081
01:23:58,784 --> 01:24:00,119
I'm looking after you.

1082
01:24:01,287 --> 01:24:03,873
You don't say, really? Looking after me?

1083
01:24:03,956 --> 01:24:06,167
Well, first I've heard of it.

1084
01:24:07,793 --> 01:24:08,961
Since when?

1085
01:24:09,754 --> 01:24:11,005
Quite a few weeks now.

1086
01:24:11,547 --> 01:24:12,965
Oh, a few weeks now?

1087
01:24:14,091 --> 01:24:15,218
Happy to hear it.

1088
01:24:16,219 --> 01:24:19,305
Amazing. Nobody ever tells me
anything in this house.

1089
01:24:20,097 --> 01:24:22,892
- I thought we were getting a new one.
- A new what?

1090
01:24:23,726 --> 01:24:25,811
Nurse. A new nurse.

1091
01:24:25,895 --> 01:24:29,190
The one who looks a bit like Lucy,
my other daughter.

1092
01:24:29,982 --> 01:24:32,735
I met her the other day.
She came here, didn't she?

1093
01:24:33,402 --> 01:24:34,695
Will you take your medication?

1094
01:24:35,279 --> 01:24:38,115
She was supposed to start this morning.

1095
01:24:38,199 --> 01:24:39,867
Laura. Wasn't she?

1096
01:24:40,451 --> 01:24:42,870
I think you're mixing things up, Anthony.

1097
01:24:42,954 --> 01:24:45,456
The one who reminds me of Lucy.

1098
01:24:46,540 --> 01:24:47,917
- Right.
- Right.

1099
01:24:48,709 --> 01:24:50,586
Time to take our medication.

1100
01:24:51,671 --> 01:24:52,505
Yeah.

1101
01:24:53,130 --> 01:24:54,715
Not timed by the minute, is it?

1102
01:25:02,014 --> 01:25:02,932
Where is Anne?

1103
01:25:04,016 --> 01:25:06,394
Your daughter isn't here, Anthony.

1104
01:25:07,979 --> 01:25:10,898
- Where is she? Has she gone out?
- If you remember,

1105
01:25:11,565 --> 01:25:13,067
she lives in Paris.

1106
01:25:14,485 --> 01:25:15,987
No. Oh, no, no, no.

1107
01:25:17,863 --> 01:25:20,366
She thought about going...

1108
01:25:21,409 --> 01:25:22,868
but in the end, it didn't happen.

1109
01:25:24,620 --> 01:25:26,747
She's been there several months now.

1110
01:25:28,332 --> 01:25:29,667
My daughter, in Paris?

1111
01:25:29,750 --> 01:25:32,253
No, no, no. They don't even speak English.

1112
01:25:32,336 --> 01:25:33,170
Look.

1113
01:25:34,130 --> 01:25:39,093
Yesterday, this postcard she sent you,
we read it together.

1114
01:25:39,176 --> 01:25:41,220
Do you remember? Look.

1115
01:25:44,640 --> 01:25:46,350
I tell you this every day.

1116
01:25:46,851 --> 01:25:49,145
She lives in Paris
because she met a man called Paul

1117
01:25:49,228 --> 01:25:51,063
and that's who she's living with now.

1118
01:25:51,647 --> 01:25:53,983
She comes to see you sometimes.

1119
01:25:54,066 --> 01:25:55,818
- Anne?
- Yes.

1120
01:25:55,901 --> 01:25:57,903
Occasionally, she comes for the weekend.

1121
01:25:57,987 --> 01:26:00,906
She comes here,
and you go for a walk in the park.

1122
01:26:00,990 --> 01:26:05,036
And she tells you about her new life,
what she's up to.

1123
01:26:06,662 --> 01:26:09,915
The other day she brought you coffee
'cause you like coffee.

1124
01:26:09,999 --> 01:26:11,500
I detest coffee.

1125
01:26:12,251 --> 01:26:13,753
I only drink tea.

1126
01:26:16,630 --> 01:26:19,467
- Everything all right?
- Fine. We were just getting dressed.

1127
01:26:21,177 --> 01:26:22,094
Everything all right?

1128
01:26:24,096 --> 01:26:24,930
Yes.

1129
01:26:27,850 --> 01:26:30,686
- There you go.
- Thank you. Have a nice day.

1130
01:26:31,479 --> 01:26:32,480
See you later.

1131
01:26:37,360 --> 01:26:39,278
Him, that one, who is he?

1132
01:26:39,779 --> 01:26:40,613
Who?

1133
01:26:42,531 --> 01:26:44,784
Him, who just left.

1134
01:26:45,618 --> 01:26:46,577
That's Bill.

1135
01:26:47,161 --> 01:26:47,995
Bill?

1136
01:26:48,621 --> 01:26:50,289
- Yeah.
- Are you sure?

1137
01:26:51,207 --> 01:26:52,249
Yes. Why?

1138
01:26:52,333 --> 01:26:53,834
Oh, no reason. I just--

1139
01:26:54,835 --> 01:26:57,004
I just, I-- How shall I put this?

1140
01:27:01,384 --> 01:27:02,760
What's he doing here?

1141
01:27:05,304 --> 01:27:07,306
Here in my flat? Do I know him?

1142
01:27:09,100 --> 01:27:11,268
He's Bill. You see him every day.

1143
01:27:12,812 --> 01:27:13,646
Do I?

1144
01:27:15,356 --> 01:27:16,732
- And you...
- What?

1145
01:27:18,192 --> 01:27:19,568
Sorry to ask this, but...

1146
01:27:20,569 --> 01:27:22,029
I mean, you, who--?

1147
01:27:23,197 --> 01:27:25,449
Who are you exactly?

1148
01:27:25,533 --> 01:27:26,659
I'm Catherine.

1149
01:27:27,535 --> 01:27:28,828
Catherine. That's right.

1150
01:27:30,037 --> 01:27:31,539
Yes, yes, yes.

1151
01:27:32,081 --> 01:27:33,082
Catherine.

1152
01:27:34,041 --> 01:27:35,668
- And he's Bill.
- Yes.

1153
01:27:42,383 --> 01:27:43,509
What about me?

1154
01:27:47,847 --> 01:27:48,681
Who...

1155
01:27:50,724 --> 01:27:52,393
exactly am I?

1156
01:27:53,853 --> 01:27:54,728
You?

1157
01:27:55,855 --> 01:27:56,814
You're Anthony.

1158
01:27:57,356 --> 01:27:58,399
Anthony?

1159
01:27:59,066 --> 01:27:59,900
Yes.

1160
01:28:01,569 --> 01:28:03,112
Anthony. It's a nice name.

1161
01:28:04,447 --> 01:28:05,823
"Anthony," don't you think?

1162
01:28:08,075 --> 01:28:09,410
It's a very nice name.

1163
01:28:10,870 --> 01:28:12,955
My mother gave it to me, I imagine.

1164
01:28:14,206 --> 01:28:15,708
- Do you know her?
- Who?

1165
01:28:16,834 --> 01:28:17,710
My mother.

1166
01:28:18,544 --> 01:28:19,837
- She...
- No.

1167
01:28:21,464 --> 01:28:22,465
She had-- She--

1168
01:28:25,301 --> 01:28:26,927
She had such big eyes.

1169
01:28:29,138 --> 01:28:30,806
I can see her face now.

1170
01:28:32,766 --> 01:28:34,435
She was-- I hope she'll...

1171
01:28:36,353 --> 01:28:37,897
come and see me sometime.

1172
01:28:38,564 --> 01:28:40,065
Do you think? Mommy.

1173
01:28:41,192 --> 01:28:45,362
You were saying she might come
occasionally at the weekend.

1174
01:28:45,446 --> 01:28:46,447
Your daughter.

1175
01:28:49,200 --> 01:28:50,075
No.

1176
01:28:53,662 --> 01:28:54,705
My mommy.

1177
01:29:03,547 --> 01:29:04,632
I want my mommy.

1178
01:29:04,715 --> 01:29:07,259
I want my mommy. I wanna get out of here.

1179
01:29:11,347 --> 01:29:14,725
Have-- Have someone come and fetch me.

1180
01:29:14,808 --> 01:29:16,018
Now...

1181
01:29:16,101 --> 01:29:19,230
No, no. I want my mommy.
I want her to come and fetch me.

1182
01:29:19,313 --> 01:29:21,440
I-- I want to go home.

1183
01:29:22,024 --> 01:29:23,400
What is it, Anthony?

1184
01:29:27,738 --> 01:29:28,739
What is it?

1185
01:29:32,201 --> 01:29:33,369
I feel as if I'm--

1186
01:29:33,994 --> 01:29:36,247
I feel as if I'm losing all my leaves.

1187
01:29:36,330 --> 01:29:37,831
- Your leaves?
- Yeah.

1188
01:29:37,915 --> 01:29:39,250
What do you mean?

1189
01:29:40,709 --> 01:29:43,045
The branches and the wind and the rain.

1190
01:29:47,216 --> 01:29:49,677
I don't know what's happening anymore.

1191
01:29:50,970 --> 01:29:52,513
Do you know what's happening?

1192
01:29:53,973 --> 01:29:55,975
All this business about the flat.

1193
01:29:56,725 --> 01:30:02,189
I... I have nowhere
to put my head down anymore.

1194
01:30:06,610 --> 01:30:10,781
But I know my watch is on my wrist,
that I do know.

1195
01:30:11,615 --> 01:30:13,158
For the journey.

1196
01:30:14,827 --> 01:30:15,911
If not, I...

1197
01:30:19,039 --> 01:30:20,291
Don't know if I'll...

1198
01:30:22,167 --> 01:30:23,377
be ready to...

1199
01:30:24,628 --> 01:30:25,504
To...

1200
01:30:34,013 --> 01:30:35,097
First...

1201
01:30:37,057 --> 01:30:38,726
we'll get dressed, shall we?

1202
01:30:38,809 --> 01:30:39,727
Yes.

1203
01:30:40,352 --> 01:30:41,604
We'll get dressed,

1204
01:30:42,229 --> 01:30:44,857
and then we'll go for a walk
in the park, shall we?

1205
01:30:44,940 --> 01:30:45,816
Yes.

1206
01:30:46,483 --> 01:30:47,359
Good.

1207
01:30:49,653 --> 01:30:51,947
The trees and all the leaves.

1208
01:30:52,531 --> 01:30:55,659
Then we'll come back here,
and we'll have something to eat.

1209
01:30:55,743 --> 01:30:56,577
Yes.

1210
01:30:57,161 --> 01:30:59,788
And then you can have
your siesta, all right?

1211
01:30:59,872 --> 01:31:00,789
Yes.

1212
01:31:03,500 --> 01:31:05,586
And then if you're feeling on good form,

1213
01:31:05,669 --> 01:31:08,172
we can go
for another little walk in the park.

1214
01:31:08,714 --> 01:31:10,424
- Just the two of us.
- Yeah.

1215
01:31:10,507 --> 01:31:12,343
Because it's such a lovely day.

1216
01:31:15,638 --> 01:31:17,139
It's sunny outside.

1217
01:31:20,934 --> 01:31:23,020
And we have to go while it's sunny.

1218
01:31:23,103 --> 01:31:25,606
- We have to take that chance.
- Yeah.

1219
01:31:25,689 --> 01:31:28,567
'Cause it never lasts long
when the weather's this good, does it?

1220
01:31:28,651 --> 01:31:29,652
No.

1221
01:31:30,402 --> 01:31:33,322
So... let's get dressed.

1222
01:31:33,405 --> 01:31:34,490
Is that all right?

1223
01:31:34,573 --> 01:31:35,908
No.

1224
01:31:35,991 --> 01:31:37,618
- Come on now.
- No.

1225
01:31:37,701 --> 01:31:39,078
Come on, baby.

1226
01:31:39,745 --> 01:31:42,081
It's all right. Come on.

1227
01:31:43,082 --> 01:31:44,041
Easy now.

1228
01:31:45,584 --> 01:31:46,418
Easy.

1229
01:31:48,962 --> 01:31:51,799
You're going to feel all right
in a minute, I promise you.

1230
01:31:53,425 --> 01:31:55,135
Everything will be all right.
